quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  42,23,"Those are the glad tidings Allah gives to His servants who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds. Say<sup>sg </sup>, “I ask of you no reward for it except the genuine love offered among those of kinship.” And whoever scores a good deed, We will increase its goodness for him; indeed, Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Ever Thankful."
  42,24,"Or do they say, “He has fabricated lies about Allah.” Yet if Allah so willed, He could seal your<sup>sg </sup>heart. But Allah erases falsehood and upholds the truth by His Words; indeed, He is All-Knowing of what lies within the chests."
  42,25,"And it is He who accepts the repentance of His servants, and pardons evil deeds, and knows what you<sup>pl </sup>do{1};",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…and knows what they do;”]
  42,26,"and He responds<i>(to) </i>those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds, and He increases them of His grace. But for the deniers is a severe punishment."
  42,27,"And if Allah were to extend provision for His servants, they would oppress<i>(others) </i>on earth. Rather, He bestows{1}from on highin precise measure whatever He wills; indeed, regarding His servants, He is All-Aware, All-Seeing.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “…but He sends down in precise measure whatever He wills…”]
  42,28,"And it is He who bestows{1}rain from on high,after they have despaired, and unfolds His mercy, and it is He Who is the Ultimate Guardian, the Praiseworthy.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Ibn Amer, Asem and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…He who sends down rain after they…”]
  42,29,"And of His signs are the creation of the heavens and the earth and the treading creatures He has spread throughout them, for He is All-Able to gather them at will."
  42,30,"And whatever disaster befalls you<sup>pl </sup>—it is because of what your hands have earned, yet He pardons much."
  42,31,"And you<sup>pl </sup>cannot thwart<i>(God) </i>on earth, and apart from Allah you have neither ally nor supporter."
